Determined to nip the problem of building collapse in the bud, the Ogun State Government has urged members of the public to volunteer information on unethical building practices that could cause loss of lives and property. The Chief Press Secretary to the state governor, Kunle Somorin, said in a statement that the governor gave the charge while speaking through the Commissioner for Physical Planning and Urban Development, Tunji Odunlami. JUST IN: Tension as protesting youths, attack travellers, kill Kaduna resident Aircraft with 133 people onboard crashes in China He noted that the state government could only put an end to untimely deaths as a result of building collapse if such unethical practices by building owners and property developers are brought to its notice.